    <section id="id678788fd979b4e8b8786f2b1d944a17a">
      <enum>3.</enum>
      <header>Funding</header>
			<subsection id="id6d8ecbabb0ef400aabf0049ca46d0fdc">
        <enum>(a)</enum>
        <header>Budgetary
			 effects</header>
        <text>The budgetary effects of this Act, for the purpose of
			 complying with the <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="act" value="Statutory Pay-As-You-Go Act of 2010">Statutory Pay-As-You-Go Act of 2010</cato:entity-ref>, shall be determined by
			 reference to the latest statement titled <quote>Budgetary Effects of PAYGO
			 Legislation</quote> for this Act, submitted for printing in the Congressional
			 Record by the Chairman of the <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="committee" entity-id="SSBU00">Senate Budget Committee</cato:entity-ref>, provided that such
			 statement has been submitted prior to the vote on passage.</text>
			</subsection>
      <subsection id="id5b1ca924625f41f0adf5ca68be560a78">
        <enum>(b)</enum>
        <header>Advance
			 appropriations required</header>
        <text>
          <cato:entity xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="auth-auth-approp">An authorization of appropriations under
			 <cato:property name="purpose">this Act or an amendment made by this Act</cato:property> shall be effective for a fiscal year
			 only to the extent and <cato:funds-and-year amount="indefinite">in the amounts provided in advance in appropriations
			 Acts</cato:funds-and-year>.</cato:entity>
        </text>
			</subsection>
    </section>
